# Spring Boot Acceptance Testing

## End-to-End API Tests
- Full application context with `@SpringBootTest(webEnvironment = RANDOM_PORT)`
- Test complete user workflows through the API
- Use `WebTestClient` or REST Assured for HTTP interactions

## Scope
- Test business scenarios end-to-end (create -> read -> update -> delete)
- Verify error scenarios and edge cases at the API boundary
- Test authentication and authorization flows

## External Dependencies
- All external services stubbed with WireMock or Testcontainers
- Database: real instance via Testcontainers
- Message brokers: Testcontainers (Kafka, RabbitMQ)

## Test Organization
- Suffix: `*AcceptanceTest.java` or `*AT.java`
- Group by feature/domain, not by endpoint
- Each test class covers a complete feature scenario

## Data Management
- Clean state before each test (truncate or recreate)
- Use test-specific data builders for realistic fixtures
- Avoid depending on test execution order

## Assertions
- Verify HTTP status codes, response bodies, headers
- Verify side effects: database state, sent messages, audit logs
- Use JSON path assertions for response structure

